notes: The paradigmatic type family. Vec(n) is the type of lists of length n.
Fin(n) is the type of natural numbers less than n. Fin(0) is empty.
Matrix(m,n) is the type of m×n matrices. Dimensions are part of the type.
Identity type. Eq(a,b) is the type of proofs that a equals b.
LessThan(m,n) is the type of proofs that m < n.
Positive(n) is the type of proofs that n > 0. Positive(0) is empty.
NonEmpty(xs) is the type of proofs that xs is not the empty list.
Sorted(xs) is the type of proofs that xs is in ascending order.
BinaryTree(n) is the type of complete binary trees of depth n.
Even(n) is the type of proofs that n is even. Even(3) is empty.
Divisible(n,d) is the type of proofs that d divides n evenly.
Type of Archive records of stakdur in a specific phase of the Quintic Cycle.
Type of Archive entries from a specific year.
Type of valid classifications for a given specimen.
